items.summary: Lots of people like this place

items.text: Phil Jaber and his son Jacob spent several months developing each blend. Phil's Tesora or "Treasure" blend took 7 years to find the perfect combination of beans.
If it's warm outside, go for the Iced Mint Mojito
Best coffee in California. BOOM. Extremely aggressive statement, extremely true. Anesthesia light cream light sugar = legitimate hangover cure
Whatever you do, don’t order a latte. At this strictly coffee-only establishment, order your date what the locals love: the Iced Mint Mojito or the Tesora. #vday
Go to Philz and try the Iced Mint Mojito Coffee... it's fabulous.
Philz Coffee on Berry Street now lets you order and pay ahead with your phone. Download the OrderAhead App.
SF Weekly's Best of Winner 2010 - Reader's Poll - BEST COFFEE
Try the off the radar coffees...Red Sea is my fave, not on the menu. And "the 49er" is half #4 Wonderbar, half #9 Canopy of Heaven.  yum.Official hangover cure: Anesthesia To The Upside
Always expect a line. This place is super busy, for good reason. Some of the best coffee around. Get the Mint Mojito Iced Coffee, sweet and creamy - you won't be disappointed.
My favorite coffee place in SF -- the Iced Mint Mojito is the way to go.  Leave your Yanks hat at home though.
The mint mojito is off the charts, but breakfast burritos take about 15 minutes to warm up :-/
Coffee is amazing. Duh. Don't get a breakfast burrito unless you have a good 10-15 minutes to wait.
Silken Soul - Silken Splendor + Philtered Soul. WOW! @philzcoffee #SF #Coffee #LEGIT
For even the non-reg coffee drinker, still easy to enjoy their diverse and tasty brews. "It's The Best" lives up to its name.
Mint mojito
Turkish is yummy
New Manhattan with almond milk is great
One more vote for the mint mojito iced coffee. It's a potent, very fresh blast of caffeine. Don't drink it too fast.
My favorite coffee shop!  I recommend the mocha tessora, and black tea with mint. It gets crowded and parking (street parking) is hard to find
Take a friend, buy them their first Mint Mojito Iced Coffee as a gift, and tell them to pay it forward.

items.name: Best Coffices in San Francisco
items.description: Got some time between meetings? Get work done at one of these coffee shops offering free wifi, power outlets to recharge your laptop, and great coffee to recharge yourself! More at http://coffices.co

items.name: Best places to study in SF
items.description: "Best" because there's usually wifi, friendly people, late hours, and electrical outlets, but most DEFINITELY this collection of places bookmarks the places with the BEST ambiance.

items.name: Free Wifi & Power in San Francisco
items.description:
A list of places with free Wifi AND power outlets in San Francisco, if you need a place to work from all day or send that last email. 

Feel free to add Wifi passwords as tips. List is ever evolving.
